<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900724-0083</DOCNO><DOCID>900724-0083.</DOCID><HL>   China's Imports Drop</HL><DATE>07/24/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><IN>MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)</IN><LP>   BEIJING -- China's imports in the first half of 1990 fellby almost one-fourth compared with the like period last year,a government official said, blaming the drop on economicsanctions imposed after China's crackdown on last year'spro-democracy movement.   China's exports, meanwhile, jumped 22% from the first halfof 1989, totaling $24.5 billion, Liu Xiangdong, spokesman forthe Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations and Trade, said.</LP><TEXT>   June's export volume of $5.32 billion was China'shighest-ever in a single month.</TEXT></DOC>